{"comments":"Internal: Declarative transition specification types.\n\nProvides ADTs for describing HOW visualizations should animate:\n- `EnterBehavior`: How new elements appear (FadeIn, ScaleUp, Instant)\n- `ExitBehavior`: How removed elements disappear (FadeOut, ScaleDown, Instant)\n- `UpdateBehavior`: How existing elements move (TransitionMove, InstantMove)\n\nBy making transitions declarative, users describe the desired end state\nand the library handles all sequencing automatically.\n\n**Internal module** - these types are used by `Hylograph.Simulation.Scene`.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[41,11],"name":"../../visualisation libraries/purescript-hylograph-selection/src/Hylograph/Internal/Transition/Scene.purs","start":[41,3]},"title":"FadeIn"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[42,12],"name":"../../visualisation libraries/purescript-hylograph-selection/src/Hylograph/Internal/Transition/Scene.purs","start":[42,3]},"title":"ScaleUp"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[43,17],"name":"../../visualisation libraries/purescript-hylograph-selection/src/Hylograph/Internal/Transition/Scene.purs","start":[43,3]},"title":"InstantEnter"}],"comments":"\nTransitions describe HOW a scene appears, not just WHAT it contains.\nBy making transitions part of the scene specification, we maintain\nthe declarative philosophy: users describe the desired end state and\nthe library handles all sequencing automatically.\n\nThis module provides general-purpose transition types that can be used\nfor any visualization, not just simulations. For simulation-specific\nscene configuration, see Hylograph.Simulation.Scene.\nHow nodes should appear when they enter the visualization\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[43,